{
  "texts": [
    "Each collision introduces a negative value to the execution time, causing a sharp decline in the overall reward.The same pattern can be seen in Figure 5.6, which shows reward function during algorithm's execution time with an A2C agent in evaluation mode in one run when diversity is included.",
    "The Figures for PPO (5.7 for training and 5.8 for evaluation) show same pattern too.",
    "The evaluation part was run 10 times.",
    "The inclusion of diversity in both PPO and A2C algorithms enhanced the WCET estimation.",
    "The superior performance of RL algorithms with diversity included (both in PPO and A2C)) over those without diversity can be attributed to several key factors."
  ]
}